President Biden is set to meet with Italian Prime Minister Mario Draghi on May 10, 2022, at the White House. The purpose of the visit is to strengthen the friendship and partnership between the United States and Italy. The leaders will discuss their ongoing coordination with allies and partners to support the people of Ukraine and impose economic consequences on Russia for its aggression. They will also focus on promoting global economic prosperity, enhancing Europe's energy security, and combating climate change. In addition, they will exchange views on regional and global security matters and prepare for the upcoming G7 and NATO summits in June.